item.title: Eva's midway update
item.description: This is my second semester joining the UCOSP with Ingres. From the lessons that I have learnt last term, I have planned my schedule out at the start from reading off the requirements of this semester and so far I am sticking to it quite well. I have completed half of the required patches. Not only I found myself matured in how to co-operate with people working oversea, but also in self-monitoring.

item.title: Eva Wong
item.description: Here is a ‘hello’ from Eva Wong for all the UCOSP buddies! I will be working with Ingres under Andrew Ross for this coming fall. I’m a fourth year computer science undergraduate student at University of Toronto, specializing in information system. I’m also doing a mathematics minor. For the previous summers in between school years, other than biking, I have been working on the GIS that I found with my team, Geokudo(2009), also I have completed a data visualization tool as a GSoC project(2008) for HackyStat.
